# PHP-MNGR 🐘

**Docker PHP Web Server Manager for Dev's & Homelabers** — companion to DB-3NGIN3

---

## What it does

PHP-MNGR lets you spin up, manage, and publish PHP websites via Docker containers — with a single click. Built for T-Mobile 5G home internet (CGNAT) where traditional port forwarding doesn't work. Sites go public through **Cloudflare Tunnels** — no open ports, no router config, no SSL setup required.

---

## Requirements

- Python 3.8+ (stdlib only — no pip dependencies)
- Docker (running)
- Cloudflare account (free) + API token
- Namecheap account (optional — for domain management)

---

## Quick Start

```bash
sg docker -c "python3 phpmanager.py"
# Opens http://localhost:4280
```

---
## Quick Fix (if container already exists)

```bash
pkill -f phpmanager.py
sg docker -c "python3 phpmanager.py"
```

## Features

### Sites
| Feature | Details |
|---|---|
| **PHP Versions** | 7.2, 7.3, 7.4, 8.0, 8.1, 8.2, 8.3 |
| **One-click create** | Spins up a `php:VERSION-apache` Docker container instantly |
| **File Manager** | Browse, edit, upload, download, rename, delete, chmod |
| **Inline editor** | Edit PHP/HTML/CSS/JS directly in the browser |
| **PHP config** | Custom `php.ini` per site |

### Domains & Tunnels
| Feature | Details |
|---|---|
| **Cloudflare Tunnels** | Publish any site publicly — works on CGNAT/T-Mobile 5G |
| **Auto DNS** | Creates CNAME record in Cloudflare automatically |
| **Free HTTPS** | SSL handled by Cloudflare — no certs to manage |
| **One-click tunnel** | Select a site, click Tunnel Now — live in seconds |
| **Custom service URL** | Tunnel any `localhost:PORT` — Node.js, Python, etc. |
| **Start/Stop tunnels** | Toggle public access without deleting the tunnel |
| **Namecheap integration** | View domains, sync DNS, add domains to Cloudflare |

---

## Architecture

```
Internet
  └── phcast.com (Cloudflare Edge)
        └── Cloudflare Named Tunnel (cloudflared container)
              └── http://localhost:8100
                    └── PHP Docker container (website)

PHP-MNGR UI → http://localhost:4280
```

**Docker containers created:**
- `<site-name>` — one `php:VERSION-apache` container per site (ports 8100+)
- `cftunnel-<site-id>` — one `cloudflare/cloudflared` container per tunnel (`--network host`)

**Data stored at `~/.phpmngr/`:**
```
~/.phpmngr/
  sites.json          ← site registry
  tunnels.json        ← tunnel registry (IDs, tokens, domains)
  cloudflare.json     ← Cloudflare API token
  namecheap.json      ← Namecheap API credentials
  sites/<id>/www/     ← web root (mounted into container)
  sites/<id>/php.ini  ← custom PHP config per site
```

---

## Cloudflare Setup

### Get an API Token
1. Go to [dash.cloudflare.com/profile/api-tokens](https://dash.cloudflare.com/profile/api-tokens)
2. Click **Create Token** → use **"Edit zone DNS"** template
3. Add permission: **Account → Cloudflare Tunnel → Edit**
4. Set **Account Resources**: All accounts
5. Set **Zone Resources**: All zones
6. Create token → copy the value
7. In PHP-MNGR → **⚙ Settings → Cloudflare** → paste & save

### Required Token Permissions
- Account → Cloudflare Tunnel → Edit
- Account → Cloudflare Tunnel → Read
- Zone → Zone → Read
- Zone → DNS → Edit
- Zone → DNS → Read

### Tunnel a Site
1. Go to **Domains & Tunnels**
2. Click **☁ Tunnel Site** on any domain in Cloudflare
3. Select your PHP site from the dropdown
4. Click **Tunnel Now** — done

---

## Namecheap Setup (optional)

Enables viewing and managing your Namecheap domains directly in PHP-MNGR.

1. Log into Namecheap → Profile → Tools → **API Access**
2. Enable API + whitelist your server IP
3. In PHP-MNGR → **⚙ Settings → Namecheap** → enter credentials

---

## Survive Reboots

Docker containers don't auto-start after reboot by default. Fix:

```bash
# Auto-restart site containers
docker update --restart unless-stopped website phpmngr-proxy

# Start PHP-MNGR manually after reboot
cd "/path/to/phpmanager"
sg docker -c "python3 phpmanager.py"
```

### Optional: systemd service
```ini
# ~/.config/systemd/user/phpmngr.service
[Unit]
Description=PHP-MNGR

[Service]
ExecStart=/usr/bin/sg docker -c "python3 /path/to/phpmanager.py"
WorkingDirectory=/path/to/phpmanager
Restart=on-failure

[Install]
WantedBy=default.target
```

```bash
systemctl --user enable --now phpmngr
```

